<h3><a name="The_Source_Text_Pane">The Source Text Pane</a></h3>

<center><img src="images/sourcetext.png" alt="The Source Text Pane">
<h5>The Source Text Pane</h5></center>

This pane is on the left hand side of the main window. It shows a tree
view of all the contexts and within each context its phrases. A second
column called "Done" is used to mark the phrases and contexts. 

An "X" next to a source phrase signifies that it has been translated and
marked as "done". An "(?)" signifies a translation which has a
validation conflict. An "(obs.)" signifies an obsolete translation, i.e.
a translation used in a previous version of the application but which is
not in the current version. 

An "X" next to a context signifies that all the phrases in that context
have been translated. A "(?)" next to a context signifies that one or
more phrases in the context have a translation validation conflict. 

The "X" mark is important since only source phrases that are marked with
it have their translations used in the application. This mark can be
added or removed from a source phrase by clicking in the "Done" column
of the source text pane to the right of the source text or by clicking
the "Done" checkbox above the command buttons. (The checkbox only
affects the source text highlighted in the source text pane.)  The "X"
mark can only be added to source texts which have a translation that
passes validation. 

The contexts are ordered alphabetically. The phrases within each context
are in the order in which they appear in the source program and this may
not be the order in which they are shown on screen. 

<h3><a name="The_Source_Text_Comments_Pane">
The Source Text and Comments Pane</a></h3>

<center><img src="images/sourcetextandcomments.png" alt="The Source Text and
