The source text and comments pane is at the top right of the main
window. It is divided into three sections. The top section shows the
source phrase. The middle section, between the two lines, shows the
programmer's comment if there is one -- this is used to disambiguate
between otherwise identical source texts. The bottom section, below
the two lines, shows the context -- this is normally a single word (the
class-name in programmer's parlance) and a comment that should contain
information about the context, e.g. how to navigate to where the text
appears in the application so that the translator can see what it looks
like.

